1. Introduction
This repository contains a modular and scalable API automation framework built with Java, Rest-Assured, TestNG, and Allure Reporting. 
It targets the Reqres public API and validates user management workflows including creation, update, retrieval, and deletion.

2. Developing frameworks
Java - OpenJDK 21.0.1
Rest-Assured - 5.5.6
TestNG - 7.11.0
Allure Reporting
Maven
IntelliJ IDEA 

3. Project structure
src/
├── main/
│   └── java/
│       ├── models/                 # DTOs for request and response
│       ├── services/              # API request methods
│       └── RestAssuredConfigurations.java
├── test/
│   ├── java/
│   │   ├── tests/                 # Test classes
│   │   └── data/Utils/           # JSON reader utility
│   └── resources/                # Test data files (JSON)
│   └── testNg.xml                # TestNG suite configuration

4. Features
Create, update, retrieve, and delete users via Reqres API

Data-driven testing using external JSON files

Centralized request configuration via RestAssuredConfigurations

Clean DTO separation: UserRequest for payloads, Users for responses

Allure integration for rich test reporting

5. How to Run Tests
Install Allure CLI (via Scoop or npm)
Run tests using TestNG suite:mvn test -DsuiteXmlFile="src/test/resources/testNg.xml"

6. To generate the report
Run through terminal: 
allure generate allure-results --clean -o allure-report
allure open allure-report

